0811                       1033 CREATE:
0811                       1034 
0811                       1035 ; Add a new node to the identifier tree. The identifier is at ID with
0811                       1036 ; bit 7 of the last character set to one. The length of the identifier is
0811                       1037 ; in LENID, which is ID-1.
0811                       1038 ;
0811                       1039 ; Node format:
0811                       1040 ;	1. Length of identifier (1 byte)
0811                       1041 ;	2. Identifier (1-80 bytes)
0811                       1042 ;	3. Left link (2-byte pointer to alphabetically smaller identifiers)
0811                       1043 ;	4. Right link (0 if none larger)
0811                       1044 ;	5. Data field:
0811                       1045 ;	   a. Defined flag (0=undefined, 1=defined)
0811                       1046 ;	   b. Value (2 bytes)
0811                       1047 ;
0811                       1048 ; This routine returns with AL=zero and zero flag set (which indicates
0811                       1049 ; on return from LOOKUP that it has not yet been defined), DX points
0811                       1050 ; to start of new node, and BX points to data field of new node.
0811                       1051 
